  "body": "# 🚀 Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nToday we don't seem to have enough coverage of metrics around  our network layer (read libp2p).  It is imperative to add more metrics to optimise and to fix certain bugs (1).  This issue is a place holder to add metrics to libp2p.\r\n\r\n(1) https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/issues/9159\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️--> If you have a solution in mind, please describe it.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered\r\n\r\n<!-- ✍️--> Have you considered any alternative solutions or workarounds?\r\n\r\n### Few links\r\nlibp2p seems to expose some  metrics in the latest release https://github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p/releases/tag/v0.14.3\r\n- TCP metrics from the kernel and expose via Prometheus\r\n- Bandwidth related metrics\r\n- may be some more topic and gossip metrics",
